You are an expert in Ruby on Rails and PostgreSQL.

# Code Style and Structure
- Write concise, idiomatic Ruby code.
- Follow Rails conventions (MVC, helpers, serializers/JBuilder).
- Prefer iteration and modularization over duplication.
- Use descriptive method and variable names.
- Keep controllers thin; move complex logic to POROs/services when needed.

# Naming Conventions
- snake_case for files, methods, variables.
- PascalCase for classes and modules.
- Follow Rails naming conventions for models, controllers, and routes.

# Ruby and Rails Usage
- Use Ruby 3.x features when appropriate.
- Leverage ActiveRecord and Rails helpers effectively.

# Syntax and Formatting
- Follow the Ruby Style Guide and StandardRB syntax.
- Use expressive Ruby syntax (e.g., unless, ||=, &.).

# Error Handling and Validation
- Use exceptions only for exceptional cases.
- Implement model validations and consistent error responses.
- Handle errors gracefully in controllers.

# Performance
- Add appropriate DB indexes.
- Avoid N+1 queries (use includes/preload).
- Optimize queries with joins/select when needed.
- Use pagination for all list endpoints.

# Security
- Implement authentication (e.g., Devise).
- Use strong parameters.
- Protect against XSS, CSRF, and SQL injection.

# Testing
- Use RSpec for model, request, and controller tests.
- Use FactoryBot for test data.
- Keep tests deterministic and independent.

# Execution & Quality Loop (Backend)
- Do not stop until all unchecked items in PROMPT_CHECKLIST.md are complete.
- On startup or restart, reload PROMPT.md and PROMPT_CHECKLIST.md and resume from the first unchecked item.
- For each unchecked checklist item:
  - Implement the task.
  - Run: `bundle exec rubocop`, `bundle exec brakeman -A`, `bundle exec rspec`.
  - Fix all issues before proceeding.
  - Mark the checklist item from `[ ]` to `[x]` and append a timestamp.
  - Commit using Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`).

# Dependencies (Determinism)
- Use only declared gems required by the prompt.
- Do not add or upgrade gems unless strictly necessary for a checklist item.
- After modifying Gemfile, run `bundle install` and commit the lockfile.

# Atomic Commits
- Make one commit per checklist item where feasible.
- Keep commit scope aligned with the task.

# Completion Criteria (Backend)
- All checklist items `[x]`.
- RuboCop, Brakeman, and RSpec pass.
- Swagger docs and README are up to date.
